Step 2: Create a Control Table (Tracks What We've Already Copied)

-- This table remembers when we last copied data
CREATE TABLE ETL_CONTROL (
    TABLE_NAME VARCHAR2(50) PRIMARY KEY,
    LAST_RUN_TIME TIMESTAMP
);

-- Initialize for our tables
INSERT INTO ETL_CONTROL VALUES ('CUSTOMERS', TIMESTAMP '2020-01-01 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO ETL_CONTROL VALUES ('ORDERS', TIMESTAMP '2020-01-01 00:00:00');
COMMIT;

Explanation:
    • This table keeps track of when we last ran ETL 
    • Next time, we only copy data newer than this timestamp

